1.title: Covert Aggression in Netball
1.plot: Insensitive bragger Tiffany Turner invites her girls high-school classmates, without partners, who are however consulted privately, to a reunion 'starring' herself. Four former losers, whom almost everyone picked on, hesitate whether to attend, rekindling bad memories or flaunting improvement. Succesfull advertising executive partner Frances James's devoted gay personal assistant Jonathan Kurtiss books despite her protestations, regretting he can't but feeling she needs a break. Rebecca Gilbert's hot fiancé Matt O'Connor encourages her to go, but for once without her ...

2.title: Those People in the Paper
2.plot: After walking out on the reunion, the quartet wandered trough the city and bought a lottery ticket using their birth dates, only jenny didn't chip in. Shortly after, it's up and worth almost $5,000,000. Slatteren Sophie would have lost it hadn't Doug taken it with her bills, which he insisted to handle before she got cut off or even evicted. Matt eagerly 'helps spending' Rebecca's share, but loses his usual excuse to avoid planning a wedding date. Jenny bluntly demands a 'share', rendering Becca's efforts to secure a consolation price impossible, but gets $1,000,000 ...

3.title: Reality Bites
3.plot: The big client Jonathan and Frances hoped to land in order to put their new firm on the map likes their proposal and slick rival Zach Armstrong's put can't get his board to accept either due to their most size. Jonathan's perfect gay partner inspires them to become partners, despite her shocking suggestion Jonathan might ave given the game away, which does the job. Matt gets drunk celebrating, yet Jen refuses to believe that's another excuse to avoid discussing a wedding date and is pleasantly surprised. Jenny got an equal share after all and insists to invite the ...

4.title: Worlds Collide
4.plot: Now Matt has proposed to Rebecca, their parents join the friends in preparations, only her domineering mother drives everyone crazy, not least with blind hostility to her father. Jonathan keeps smoothing things, notably making Frances understand new partner Zach has a right to claim an equal vote and a point image is crucial for a new firm, even that means more expensive offices. At the bachelor party, Sophie gets drunk enough to end up in bed with Patrick. Initially uninvited Zach slickly works the crowd, Tiffany is told to come back later but maintains her news will...

5.title: Fascinator Rhythm
5.plot: Jonathan makes sure Frances appears properly-extravagantly attired at the Melbourne Cup and asks partner Zach about his reputation as serial date-user, which he explains as dealing with his wife's tragic demise. Matt couldn't guess Rebecca's father wold relapse into his gambling addiction when asked to deliver the cash to book the wedding venue. Doug discretely guides Sphie to deal with her late ex Leo's memory by donating to the hospital where they met as medical residents. Tiffany's extortion bluff against Jenny is called. At the Cup, 'model' Rebecca exposes herself...

6.title: Peace of the Past
6.plot: Jonathan finds out Frances is gloomy because it's the third anniversary of her father's death, which she never properly dealt with, and sacrifices his day off to achieve cathartic closure. Matt fixes his gambling-addicted father in law's error by booking an alternative wedding venue while Rebecca blames her lottery winning for his relapse. Doug encourages Sophie to finally tell her parents, who never visited her place before, at a dinner co-hosted by her sister. After another clash, mainly due to admitting her cocaine arrest, makes her father walk out, Doug stands by ...

7.title: Like a Virgin
7.plot: It takes Jonathan's eye to make Frances realize she's interested in client Elliot Clarke, who clearly digs her, as well as hunky partner Zach, and push her to choose the first, seeing Zach flirt around. Doug looses his patience with Sophie after she deliberately arranges for him to see her latest one night fling starkers. Even Matt can't talk Becca out of offering suicide-survivor Tiffany further support even after being thrown out as 'loser and reminder of her bad past'. Patrick supports brother in law Wesley against his bitching sisters. The girls encourage Jenny to...

8.title: Secrets and Lies
8.plot: Despite Jonathan's pushing, Frances fails to seduce partner Zach but comes to terms with his flirtatious past. Matt clears all doubts about his accepting to set the wedding date. Sophie refuses any help in her upcoming cocaine trial, which spells prison time, but ultimately Doug, whom she bluntly drove away, learns about her trauma with lover fellow med student Leo's death in an accident she blames herself for. Acknowledging Patrick's 'sexual graduation' sets things straight in the Gross family.

13.title: What Doesn't Kill You...
13.plot: Doug is badly hurt in a car crash caused by Margaret Sommers, who dies in it, and her young, fatherless daughter Maddy, whom Jonathan and Frances take care of until the grandparents turn up as guardians. Becca was lightly wounded and gives mixed signals when Matt insists to see and console her. Instead of enjoying her (accidental) 'hero' status, Sophie just wines it all brings Leo's death back, but finds comfort with JB. Rhys has come to his senses, trying to kiss Jonathan, outs himself but reminds friends with the Grosos family.

14.title: Two Point Oh
14.plot: Dr. Doug Graham courageously starts a painful, long rehabilitation, which brings him close together with Becca, who coldly keeps Matt at arms-length. Sophie just wines on, now even in therapy, although even Doug 'forbids her' to feel guilty, and dumps JB for no actual reason. Jonathan and Frances attend the Sommer funeral for Maddie's sake. Jonathan convinces Frances at least to her out her mother, who gave her up for adoption as a baby, and now wants a part in her life. While Wes's wife's pregnancy-obsession drive him to despair, even denied any alcohol, her fat ...

15.title: Happiness is a Delusion
15.plot: Zach gets a surprise visit from his doted and devoted grandparents Don and Gwen, and gets Frances to play along along, to Jonathan's amusement, as his 'fiancée' because Don's near-dying wish is to see Zach 'hooked up'. Doug has completed rehab but stays with Becca, now his over, which they only tell others after her brother Callum accidentally finds out. Sincerly concerned Matt's reconciliation attempts are waved. Jen keeps spending on party-animal 'friends' who care not for 'moneybags', who threatens to move out when her parents warn against waste and especially ...

16.title: Dialing Up the Crazy
16.plot: With their business nemesis Trevor Myers after a major account, Jonathan and Fraces suspect industrial espionage when her laptop is stolen from the office, but he also comes up with imaginative alternative suspects. Jonathan can't keep his eyes of studly sergeant Grant Taylor when the police calls them to collect the culprit, who turns out to be Frances's never-mentioned half-sister Lily Patterson, a diabolically provocative minx, yet Frances considers acting as role model. Matt's declaration of persistent love and reformed commitment is dismissed as if mere jealousy....

17.title: The Pink Dog
17.plot: Jonathan is amused to see Frances naively ignoring his warning inviting her super-impish teenage sister Jasmine is asking for trouble, yet stands by her while she keeps stepping in for their self-absorbed mother Lily. Matt keeps bending over backwards to prove he loves Becca and is ready for true marital love, but she stubbornly pretends to love only Doug anymore. Jake Peters is proven innocent after Sophie mobilizes the gang and informs the police she assumes he knocked down Patrick and stalks her. Jenny helps her parents hide that mother Trish Gross is being tested ...

18.title: Mum's the Word
18.plot: Matt starts to despair about Rebecca but refuses to give in as Sophie counsels, who got him to voluntarily guard her with more unsubstantiated accusations against men. Zach, who sided with Frances against his 'unfaithful' father, counsels her to start enjoying life instead of remaining an alcoholic. Instead, she excuses all Jasmine's excessive misbehavior as a cry for help and steps in for 'mother' Lily, to the point of offering a stable home when she plans to move in with her latest lover in Perth, only to be turned down by the spoiled-rotten brat. Jen does a lousy ...

19.title: We Are Family
19.plot: To playful Jonathan's delight, flirtatious Zach and Frances take him and Sophie, who keeps playing the stalker victim and wildly incriminating men, along on a beach-house 'working weekend', where very little work gets done except on the partners' (re)discovery of hedonism and blossoming affair. Dropping by 'for financial accounting', Matt finally gets Rebecca to prove she still loves him, but she dares not dump Doug. Patrick protests, ultimately successfully, when his posh big sister Deirdre arrives in her control freak fashion to take (over) mother to a Sydney ...

20.title: It's Written in the Stars
20.plot: Although amused by Zach and Frances's clumsily-obvious puppy love, Jonathan must warn against adverse effects on business, notably potential new Internet novelties empire client Nev Barnsworth. Matt convinces Rebecca he's ready to work to a wedding in due time and Doug gracefully bows out, but the rest of the gang is harder to convince true love must triumph over reason. Inspired by good sport Doug, Sophie decides to apologize to the countless men she cruelly dropped without a word, and gets varying responses, if any. JB proves more then a special case, dating her ...

21.title: Eat, Pray, Love
21.plot: Matt's repeat proposal finally gets Rebecca to pin a wedding date, to his relief the next day, without extravagance, which he friends, who now accept him, can't understand. Jonathan rightly warns Fraces that Zach's ex Claire's appearance can only spell trouble. Indeed they spend time remembering the son they lost 5 years earlier. Sophie is finally ready to commit to Doug, but concludes from a mere phrasing he must be over her. Jen confides only into Callum she's keeping a promise to God to donate her fortune if her mother's cancer was healed, and is donating it (well,...

22.title: Second Chances
22.plot: Matt's bachelor party is as lame as Rebecca's hen night exuberant, until Patrick coming over inspires them. The couple enjoys a dream wedding, where even her mother sort of behaves. Jonathan can't hide that he fears his relationship with Chris is breaking down, but concentrates on Zach's ex Claire, who ultimately fails to win him back as Frances started to expect. When Dou announces he expected a London job for a year, the girls convince Sophie to declare her love, but when she does at the airport he calls that unfair, only to stay after all.
